     <body>
     <div type="prefatory_verse_or_poem">
   <pb facs="3"/>
   <head>A Warning-Piece.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>RIght noble <hi>Nobles,</hi> Generous <hi>Gentlemen,</hi>
      </l>
      <l>Louers of <hi>Honor,</hi> and Your <hi>Countries</hi> Weal;</l>
      <l>You'l need no <hi>VVarning</hi> to auoid our <hi>Peal;</hi>
      </l>
      <l>Nor are in <hi>Leuel</hi> of our <hi>Poudered</hi> Pen:</l>
      <l>Nor <hi>Those</hi> that Yet will <hi>yeeld,</hi> and turne agen</l>
      <l>From th' <hi>Idol-Seruice</hi> of their <hi>Smoaky Zeal,</hi>
      </l>
      <l>To serue their <hi>GOD,</hi> their <hi>KING,</hi> their <hi>Cōmon-weale</hi>
      </l>
      <l>We shoot at <hi>Manners,</hi> we would saue the <hi>Men.</hi>
      </l>
      <l>But, Those <hi>rebellious</hi> that will still <hi>stand out</hi>
      </l>
      <l>Vnder the <hi>Standard</hi> of our Heathen Foe,</l>
      <l>With <hi>Pipe</hi> and <hi>Pudding</hi> rampir'd round about,</l>
      <l>
         <hi>Puffing</hi> &amp; <hi>Snuffing</hi> at their threatned <hi>VVoe;</hi>
      </l>
      <l>At such, our <hi>Canon</hi> shall Here <hi>thunder</hi> thick:</l>
      <l>
         <hi>Gunner,</hi> your Lin-stock, Come, <hi>giue Fier quick.</hi>
      </l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>
         <hi>Tis best Praise-worthy, To haue pleas'd the Best:</hi>
      </l>
      <l>This Wee endeauour; and defie the rest.</l>
   </lg>
</div>
